# {{.ProjectName}}

Claude plugin generated by [plugin-kit-ai](https://github.com/plugin-kit-ai/plugin-kit-ai) `init`.

## Build

```bash
go mod edit -replace=github.com/plugin-kit-ai/plugin-kit-ai/sdk=<absolute-path-to>/sdk/plugin-kit-ai
go test ./...
go build -o bin/{{.ProjectName}} ./cmd/{{.ProjectName}}
```

## Claude

This scaffold wires the generated binary in router mode:

- `SessionStart`
- `SessionEnd`
- `Notification`
- `PostToolUse`
- `PostToolUseFailure`
- `PermissionRequest`
- `SubagentStart`
- `SubagentStop`
- `PreCompact`
- `Setup`
- `Stop`
- `PreToolUse`
- `TeammateIdle`
- `TaskCompleted`
- `UserPromptSubmit`
- `ConfigChange`
- `WorktreeCreate`
- `WorktreeRemove`

If you move the project, update `hooks/hooks.json` so the command points at `{{.Entrypoint}}`.
